- Write all issues as user stories ("As a <type of user> I want <something>, so that <reason>"). 
- Add acceptance criteria to accomplish the issue
- Do not include writing tests or documentation as acceptance criteria

Examples:
# Fix navbar on non-index marketing pages

As a visitor, I want to be able to navigate back to the homepage from non-index marketing pages, so that I can navigate around the site in an easy manner. 

## Acceptance Criteria

1. It is possible to navigate to "Demo", "FAQ", etc from the privacy policy, ToS, and changelog pages
---
# Support favorite projects

As a host, I want to be able to select my favorited projects so that I can easily estimate the workflow that best suits me.

## Acceptance Criteria

1. Favorite projects appear in the dropdown list.
2. The dropdown is reorganized to display items in the following order:
   * Teams
   * Projects
   * Views
